The paper discusses the security of communication systems and employs an information theoretical approach to evaluate the security. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of randomness and coding techniques, which are also relevant to the categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Coding Theory (cs.CY). The paper also mentions the use of wire-tap encoders, which are relevant to the category of Signal Processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of mobile telephony as a motivating example, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
